y reviewing the record in this case, we find that there was insufficient evidence to warrant a jury instruction on self-defense. There is no evidence from which a jury might reasonably conclude that Jacinto had a bona fide belief that he was in imminent danger of bodily harm. Accordingly, the trial court did not abuse its discretion or otherwise err in failing to give a self-defense jury instruction."
}
